13"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cause, to effect, to trigger, to generate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cable, rope","tags":["Classical"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cause, grounds, aetiological reason","examples":[{"text":"بِسَبَب ذٰلِكَ","english":"because of that"},{"text":"وَكَانَ سَبَبُ قَتْلِهِ أَنَّ أَبَاهُ اسْتَعْمَلَهُ عَلَى الْأَنْدَلُسِ، كَمَا ذَكَرْنَا، عِنْدَ عَوْدِهِ إِلَى الشَّامِ، فَضَبَطَهَا وَسَدَّدَ أُمُورَهَا، وَحَمَى ثُغُورَهَا، وَافْتَتَحَ فِي إِمَارَتِهِ مَدَائِنَ بَقِيَتْ بَعْدَ أَبِيهِ،","english":"\"And the reason for his killing was that his father had appointed him over Al-Andalus, as we have mentioned, upon his return to Ash-Sham, so he brought it under control and set its affairs in order, and protected its frontiers, and opened during his emirate cities that remained after his father,\""}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alibi"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew סיבה (sibá, “cause, reason”)."},"ipa":["/sab.ba.ba/","/sa.bab/"]}